										README
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This repository contains code for assignment 2 for CSL781: Computer Graphics Course under supervision of Prof. Prem Kalra at Indian Institute of Technology,
Delhi.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Collaborators:
Shantanu Chaudhary (2010CS50295)
Mukesh Kumar (2010CS50288)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Folder hierarchy:

Makefile	: For building, cleaning project

README		: Information about project code

src		: contains source code files

config      : contains config files for program input and configuration

obj		: contains object code files (Not under version tracker)

include		: library headers for the corresponding src code files

bin		: contains the build binary file (Not under version tracker)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Format of Configuration File:
Refer configuration files in the config/ directory

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Building the Program:

Default Build: (without supersampling)
    Use "make build" for building the program with default parameters (without supersampling)

Supersampling Enabled build: (with supersampling)
    Use "make supersample LEVEL=X" where X defines the LEVEL of supersampling. Default is 500. (Max Tested is 1000)

Executing the program:
    Use "make run CONFIG=X" where X is the name of the configuration file. The configuration file must be placed in the config folder.

Creating a debug build:
    Use "make gdb" to compile a binary with debug symbols to be used with gdb.

Debugging the program:
    Use "make debug" to first compile a binary with debug symbols and run the program in gdb for debugging.

Cleaning the build:
    Use "make clean" to remove the build binaries and object files.
